#CMVCPATHNAME com.ibm.ws.security.token.ltpa/resources/com/ibm/ws/security/token/ltpa/internal/resources/LTPAMessages.nlsprops
#COMPONENTPREFIX CWWKS
#COMPONENTNAMEFOR WebSphere Application Server Security Token Service
#ISMESSAGEFILE TRUE
#NLS_MESSAGEFORMAT_VAR
#NLS_ENCODING=UNICODE
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Message prefix block: CWWKS4100 - CWWKS4199

LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_FACTORY=CWWKS4100E: There is no initialized token factory.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_FACTORY.explanation=The token factory was not initialized.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_FACTORY.useraction=Validate the Token Manager configuration in the server.xml file, or any other resource specified by the configuration.

LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID=CWWKS4101E: There is no unique ID with which to create the token.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID.explanation=The unique_id parameter is null or was not specified in the token data.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID.useraction=Validate that the user has a unique ID. If using a custom user registry, validate that the token data contains a value for the unique_id parameter.

LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_MISSING_KEY=CWWKS4102E: The system cannot create the LTPA token because the required {0} property is missing.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_MISSING_KEY.explanation=The specified key is missing, so the LTPA token cannot be created.
LTPA_TOKEN_SERVICE_MISSING_KEY.useraction=Explore the properties file in which the LTPA key information is stored, and check that the key information includes a secret key, a private key and a public key.

LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_START=CWWKS4103I: Creating the LTPA keys. This may take a few seconds.
LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_START.explanation=The LTPA keys do not exist and are generated automatically. Any services requiring LTPA will not start until the LTPA keys have been generated and the configuration is ready.
LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_START.useraction=No action is required.

LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_COMPLETE=CWWKS4104A: LTPA keys created in {0} seconds. LTPA key file: {1}
LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_COMPLETE.explanation=This message is for informational purposes only.
LTPA_CREATE_KEYS_COMPLETE.useraction=No action is required.

LTPA_CONFIG_READY=CWWKS4105I: LTPA configuration is ready after {0} seconds.
LTPA_CONFIG_READY.explanation=This message is for informational purposes only.
LTPA_CONFIG_READY.useraction=No action is required.

LTPA_CONFIG_ERROR=CWWKS4106E: LTPA configuration error. Unable to create or read LTPA key file: {0}
LTPA_CONFIG_ERROR.explanation=The LTPA keys could not be read or created at the specified location.
LTPA_CONFIG_ERROR.useraction=Ensure the location is accessible by the server process. Any FFDCs might indicate a fatal error in generating or loading the keys.

LTPA_KEYS_TO_LOAD=CWWKS4107A: The LTPA configuration is modified. The following files are modified: {0}. All the LTPA keys in the LTPA configuration are reloaded.
LTPA_KEYS_TO_LOAD.explanation=The LTPA keys files must be reloaded due to a change to the LTPA keys files or the configuration.
LTPA_KEYS_TO_LOAD.useraction=Ensure that all servers that participate in single sign-on share the same LTPA keys and password.

LTPA_KEY_CREATE_ERROR=CWWKS4108E: The system cannot create the LTPA key.
LTPA_KEY_CREATE_ERROR.explanation=The LTPA key cannot be created.
LTPA_KEY_CREATE_ERROR.useraction=Any FFDCs might indicate a fatal error in generating the keys.

LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_IS_IN_THE_PAST=CWWKS4109W: The {0} value for the validUntilDate attribute for the {1} LTPA validation keys file is in the past. The LTPA validation keys cannot be used.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_IS_IN_THE_PAST.explanation=The LTPA validation keys are used only if the validUntilDate attribute value is in the future.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_IS_IN_THE_PAST.useraction=Update the validUntilDate attribute value to a future date if the LTPA keys must be used. Otherwise, delete the LTPA keys file.

LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_INVALID_FORMAT=CWWKS4110E: The {0} value for the validUntilDate attribute for the {1} LTPA validation keys file has an invalid date format. The LTPA validation keys cannot be used.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_INVALID_FORMAT.explanation=The validUntilDate attribute value must be formatted in the ISO date, time, and zone format. The following example shows the ISO date format: "2023-11-18T18:08:35Z".
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_VALID_UNTIL_DATE_INVALID_FORMAT.useraction=Update the validUntilDate attribute value to the ISO date, time, and zone format (e.g., '2023-11-18T18:08:35Z')

LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_MISSING_ATTR=CWWKS4111E: The {0} LTPA validationKeys element that is specified in the server.xml file is missing either the filename, password, or both: {1}.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_MISSING_ATTR.explanation=The LTPA validationKeys element requires the filename and password attributes.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_MISSING_ATTR.useraction=Add the missing attributes.

LTPA_KEYS_FILE_DOES_NOT_EXIST=CWWKS4112E: The {0} LTPA validation keys file does not exist.
LTPA_KEYS_FILE_DOES_NOT_EXIST.explanation=The validation keys file does not exist.
LTPA_KEYS_FILE_DOES_NOT_EXIST.useraction=Make sure that the validation keys file exists in the specified location that is specified by the validationKeys element.

LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_POLLED_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_NOT_ENABLED=CWWKS4113W: The LTPA updateTrigger attribute is set to polled, monitorValidationKeysDir is set to true, but monitorInterval is set to {0}. No dynamic reload occurs when LTPA key files are modified.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_POLLED_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_NOT_ENABLED.explanation=The value for the monitorInterval attribute is zero or less than zero. The directory cannot be monitored for any modifications on files with the .keys suffix and dynamic reload cannot occur.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_POLLED_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_NOT_ENABLED.useraction=Set the monitorInterval attribute to an interval that is greater than zero.

LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE=CWWKS4114W: The updateTrigger attribute is set to disabled and the monitorValidationKeysDir attribute is set to true. No dynamic reload occurs when LTPA key files are modified in the directory.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE.explanation=When the updateTrigger attribute is set to disabled, the directory is not monitored for any modifications to files with the .keys suffix and dynamic reload does not occur. Even if the monitorValidationKeysDir attribute is set to true, the attribute is ignored, and the directory is not monitored.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_VALIDATION_KEYS_DIR_TRUE.useraction=Set the value of the updateTrigger attribute to polled or mbean.

LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_GREATER_THAN_ZERO=CWWKS4115W: The updateTrigger attribute is set to disabled and the monitor interval is greater than {0}. No dynamic reload occurs when LTPA key files are modified.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_GREATER_THAN_ZERO.explanation=When the updateTrigger attribute is set to disabled, the files are not monitored for any modifications on files with the .keys suffix and dynamic reload does not occur. Even if the monitorInterval attribute is set to an interval that is greater than zero, the attribute is ignored, and the files are not monitored.
LTPA_UPDATE_TRIGGER_DISABLED_AND_MONITOR_INTERVAL_GREATER_THAN_ZERO.useraction=Set the value of the updateTrigger attribute to polled or mbean.

LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE=CWWKS4116W: The {0} validation keys must be regenerated using cryptographic algorithms that are FIPS 140-3 certified.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE.explanation=The LTPA validation keys that are created without FIPS 140-3 enabled fail when FIPS 140-3 is enabled.
LTPA_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE.useraction=Use the securityUtility createLTPAKeys command to create the FIPS approved validation keys when FIPS 140-3 is configured.

LTPA_FIPS_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE=CWWKS4117W: The {0} validation keys must be regenerated using cryptographic algorithms that are not FIPS 140-3 certified.
LTPA_FIPS_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE.explanation=The LTPA validation keys that are created with FIPS 140-3 enabled fail when FIPS 140-3 is disabled.
LTPA_FIPS_VALIDATION_KEYS_NEED_TO_REGENERATE.useraction=Use the securityUtility createLTPAKeys command to create the non FIPS approved validation keys when FIPS 140-3 is disabled.

LTPA_KEYS_PASSWORD_ERROR=CWWKS4118E: LTPA configuration error. A keysPassword attribute is not configured on the <ltpa /> element, the 'ltpa_keys_password' environment variable is not set, and the 'keystore_password' environment variable is not set.
LTPA_KEYS_PASSWORD_ERROR.explanation=The LTPA configuration requires a password to store and read LTPA keys.
LTPA_KEYS_PASSWORD_ERROR.useraction=Configure the keysPassword attribute in the <ltpa /> element, or set the 'ltpa_keys_password' or 'keystore_password' environment variables to provide a password.

LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT=CWWKS4119I: The {0} LTPA keys are being re-encrypted by using the ''keystore_password'' environment variable.
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT.explanation=The LTPA keys are being re-encrypted by using the 'keystore_password' because the default value for the LTPA keysPassword attribute is removed to improve security.
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT.useraction=No action is required.

LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_SUCCESS=CWWKS4120I: Successfully re-encrypted the {0} LTPA keys by using the ''keystore_password'' environment variable.
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_SUCCESS.explanation=The LTPA keys are re-encrypted by using the 'keystore_password' environment variable.
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_SUCCESS.useraction=If you are sharing the LTPA keys between servers in a common location, the other servers must be updated so they can continue to read those LTPA keys. Set the keysPassword attribute in the corresponding <ltpa /> element, or the password attribute in the corresponding <validationKeys /> element, to the value of the 'keystore_password' environment variable from this server. The 'keystore_password' environment variable is typically defined in the server.env file.

LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_ERROR=CWWKS4121E: Failed to re-encrypt the {0} LTPA keys. Exception: {1}
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_ERROR.explanation=The LTPA keys could not be re-encrypted. For more information, see the exception in the message.
LTPA_TOKEN3_FACTORY_NO_HYBRID_KEYS=CWWKS4122E: LTPA Token3 factory cannot create tokens because hybrid keys (RSA + ML-DSA + ML-KEM) are not configured.
LTPA_TOKEN3_FACTORY_NO_HYBRID_KEYS.explanation=The LTPA Token3 factory requires hybrid keys combining RSA, ML-DSA (quantum-resistant signatures), and ML-KEM (quantum-resistant key encapsulation) to create Post-Quantum Cryptography (PQC) tokens. The primary hybrid keys were not initialized.
LTPA_TOKEN3_FACTORY_NO_HYBRID_KEYS.useraction=Ensure that the LTPA configuration includes hybrid keys. Use the securityUtility createLTPAKeys command with the --pqc option to generate hybrid keys, or configure the ltpa element with keysFileName pointing to a valid hybrid keys file.
LTPA_KEYS_REENCRYPT_ERROR.useraction=Ensure that the LTPA keys file and its directory are not read-only. If the LTPA keys file and its directory are not read-only, then see the exception in the message for more information.
